DPRK Government Will Strive for Peace 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun, who is leading a DPRK delegation to the ministerial meeting of the 14th ASEAN regional forum, said at the meeting that the DPRK government will continue to closely cooperate with the member states of the forum including ASEAN countries for the peace on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of the region in the idea of its external policy for independence, peace and friendship in the future, too. It is indispensable for the ASEAN regional forum to thoroughly keep the essential principles of respect of sovereignty, non-interference in other's internal affairs, peaceful co-existence and ban on the use of force in order to fulfill its mission as a unique forum for political dialogue in the region, Pak said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One of the main instable factors present in Asia is none other than Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is duty-bound to redress its unprecedented past crimes by making due apology and compensation as it is a war criminal state which committed hideous crimes against humanity such as killing a great number of people and reducing hundreds of thousands of women into sexual slaves after invading Asia in the last century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the present Japanese authorities, not content with concealing and beautifying the past crimes, made no scruple of distorting the history, challenging the international community. This arouses resentment and vigilance against Japan among Asian countries which had undergone its invasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Especially, the frantic suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) rampant in every part of Japan is a grave provocation against the DPRK and an act of infringing upon its sovereignty, which no preceding Japanese government dared to do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan continues to be keen on its crackdown upon Chongryon, the DPRK can not but warn Japan that it would bring about a more serious political crisis than the financial sanctions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula is the behests of President Kim Il Sung and it is the invariable stand of the DPRK government to settle the nuclear issue through dialogue and negotiation. The denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula is, in essence, the issue directly connected with the end of the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK and removal of nuclear threat to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling the adoption of the Feb. 13 agreement, Pak reaffirmed the DPRK government's firm will to honor its commitments under the agreement.

Lao Parliamentary Delegation Leaves  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the National Assembly of the Lao People's Democratic Republic led by Thongsing Thammavong, president of the National Assembly who is member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, left here for home today after winding up its 5-day visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While staying in the DPRK, the delegation visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung, Mangyongdae, the Arch of Triumph, the Grand People's Study House and the Three-Revolution Exhibition, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also appreciated the grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang."

Visits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A government economic delegation of the DPRK led by Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man left here today to visit Iran and Syria. A delegation of the Workers' Party of Korea led by Cha Yong Myong, vice department director of the Central Committee of the WPK, also left here today to visit Laos, Malaysia and Indonesia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arriving here today was a delegation of the Secretariat of the International Institute of the Juche Idea led by its Secretary General Kenichi Ogami and a delegation of the Japanese Society for the Study of the Juche Idea led by Soko Shimabukuro, advisor of the Okinawa Socialist Masses' Party.

Settlement of Case of Detained Civilians Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly made public a statement on August 1 in which it denounced the U.S. and the south Korean authorities for shunning the issue of saving the civilians detained in Afghanistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that some of them were killed, the statement held that this was caused by the south Korean authorities' dispatch of troops to Afghanistan pursuant to the U.S. policy of invasion of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To rescue them it is necessary for the authorities to decide to withdraw the troops at once and opt for scrapping the south Korea-U.S. "alliance", it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the Council of south Korean Youth Organizations and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification separately called press conferences near the U.S. embassy in Seoul and urged the U.S. to come out for the settlement of the above-said case. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Letters of protest to the U.S. government were read out at the conferences in which they said that the U.S. is chiefly to blame for the case as it forced south Korea to dispatch troops under the signboard of "alliance." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the conferences the representatives of the organizations conveyed the letters of protest to the U.S. embassy.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Bringing Earlier Korea's Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- The three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo clearly indicate the way of the Korean nation for independent reunification. The three principles constitute the three charters for national reunification as they systematized and dealt with the fundamental principles and ways of national reunification in an integral way on the basis of the great Juche idea and the precious experience gained by President Kim Il Sung in the course of the struggle for national reunification, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three charters for national reunification are consistent with the spirit of national independence the core of which is the sovereignty and dignity of the nation and embody the noble patriotic spirit to achieve the reunification of the country in a peaceful way through national reconciliation and unity, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles of national reunification which the north and the south affirmed and solemnly declared at home and abroad in the July 4 joint statement indicate the fundamental stand and ways to be maintained by the Korean nation in the settlement of the reunification question. The ten-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation which expounds the aim of great national unity and its ideological foundation and the principles and ways of unity help further increase the driving force for national reunification and immensely enhance its role. The proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo gives a clear exposition of the full appearance of a reunified state and the ways for its materialization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The proposals for national reunification put forward by the President have powerfully encouraged all the fellow countrymen to the nationwide struggle for independent reunification and glorified annals of the reunification movement with victory of pro-reunification patriotic forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His line and policies for national reunification are the most precious legacies left by him for the Korean nation and they serve as a reliable boon for the accomplishment of the cause of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The line and policies clearly indicate the way of achieving the reunification and prosperity of the country and realizing national sovereignty and unity by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation and greatly encourage the fellow countrymen to the struggle to implement the June 15 joint declaration.

Vanguard for Reunification Active in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- The "2007 Vanguard for Peace and Reunification of the Korean Peninsula" reportedly got into action in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A "ceremony of forming the vanguard for reunification and declaring its struggle for August" took place in Seoul on August 1 under the sponsorship of the preparatory committee for the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration read out at the ceremony noted that a turning phase for national reunification has been brought about thanks to the nation-wide struggle of all the fellow countrymen, and called upon the people of different social standings to conduct an unflinching struggle aimed at withdrawing the U.S. troops, the root cause of war, from south Korea and building durable peace mechanism on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The central and regional vanguard consisted of representatives of organizations of people of different social standings including workers, peasants and youth and students would travel several regions to conduct more active struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops and the movement for national reunification, the declaration said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony, the central and regional vanguard separately held marches.

DPRK Women's Football Team Beats Rival of Taipei of China  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- The DPRK women's football team beat the rival of Taipei of China 6:0 in the Asian Regional qualifier of Group B for the 29th Olympics held in Taipei of China on August 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK team will play the last qualifier for the Olympics with the rival of Hong Kong of China in Pyongyang on August 12.

Letter of Solidarity to Pyongyang Mission of AINDF 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Chairman of the Switzerland-Korea Committee Martin Lotscher sent a solidarity letter to the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front on July 28 on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his letter wrote that the Korean people became the first in history to shatter to smithereens the myth of the U.S. imperialists' "mightiness" under the outstanding leadership of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter noted that the great Juche idea and the Songun idea based on it served as an efficient treasured sword that enabled a sovereign country to protect the freedom from the imperialist aggression and win victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialist warmongers reinvade the DPRK, the Korean People's Army will sweep away them from the surface of the earth to the last man as it has won only victory under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, the letter stressed.

DPRK's Day of Victory in War Observed in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Lectures were given in Egypt and Tanzania and a photo exhibition was held in Uganda from July 21 to 26 on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue of the photo exhibition were photos showing the Songun revolutionary leadership feats of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos introducing the invincible might of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Secretary General of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association Yehia Zakaria Khairullah in his lecture stressed that the Korean people could defeat the U.S. imperialists who boasted of being the "strongest" in the world and win great victory entirely thanks to the outstanding commanding art of President Kim Il Sung and the firm unity of the whole army and all people around the great leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Tanzanian National Coordinating Committee of the Juche Idea Study Groups Francis Fanuel Lyimo in his lecture said that Korean-style socialism has been consolidated to be an unconquerable bastion and the Korean People's Army has grown to be an invincible army capable of beating back any formidable enemy under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Sports Contest for Jonsung Cup Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) --A sports contest for the Jonsung Cup was held in Pyongyang and Wonsan on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants competed in 8 events including swimming, diving, synchronized swimming, rowing, canoeing and cycling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sports group of the Ministry of Fisheries proved successful in swimming, diving and synchronized swimming, that of the Ministry of Land and Marine Transport in rowing and canoeing and that of the Ministry of Light Industry in cycling.

International Diploma and Certificate Conferred upon Korean Artist
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The 10th Beijing international art exhibition held in China from July 12 to 16 awarded the diploma "Ten Most Famous Artists," top prize of the exhibition, and certificate to Labour Hero and Merited Artist Kim Tong Hwan, head of the Korean Painting Creative Group of the Mansudae Art Studio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He presented to the exhibition several Korean paintings such as "Girls Full of Pride" and "On the Way to Work Site." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition brought together various art organizations and artists from over 20 countries and regions.

Military Authorities' Sycophantic Submission under Fire in South Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Civic and public organizations of south Korea including the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification reportedly called a joint press conference in Seoul on July 30 to denounce the military authorities for their sycophantic submission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference speeches were made to be followed by the reading out of a letter of protest to the minister of "National Defense." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the south Korean military authorities of holding on the same day negotiations with the U.S. over the issue of disposing of reserve war materiel of the U.S. forces in south Korea, the letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military authorities are claiming that the majority of the war materiel is still usable and the quantity of the materiel to be disposed of is no more than 10 percent. This means the negotiations are conducted on the premise that south Korea would take over the whole quantity of the materiel to be scrapped by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter urged the military authorities to send back to the U.S. all the reserve war materiel as it would only cause serious environmental pollution and bring damage to the residents of the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the conference representatives of the civic and public organizations conveyed the letter to the "Ministry of National Defense."

Cancellation of Plan for War Maneuvers Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Press Headquarters of the South Side Committee of the Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement on July 30 at which it demanded the cancellation of the plan for the "Ulji Focus Lens" joint military exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement accused the U.S. and the south Korean bellicose forces of planning to stage the above-said exercises involving huge armed forces using south Korea as an operational theatre from August 20 to 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite impudent for the military authorities to join the U.S. in the war maneuvers to meet its interests only, instead of paying attention to the grave situation in Afghanistan where south Korean civilians are meeting deaths after being kidnapped, it said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We cannot repress our resentment at the U.S. and the south Korean military authorities planning to stage war exercises targeted against the north despite the fact that efforts for ensuring peace on the Korean Peninsula are more urgently required than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement demanded the U.S. and the south Korean warlike forces drop at once the above-mentioned plan.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Papers today dedicate editorials to the tenth anniversary of Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Elaborately clarified in the work are the principles arising in defending the idea of national reunification put forward by President Kim Il Sung and his leadership feats and implementing his Juche-based line and policies for national reunification including the issue of settling the question of the country's reunification on the principle of national independence, the issue of building a strong driving force for national reunification through great national unity, the issue of achieving the reunification in a peaceful way, not using force of arms and the issue of realizing the reunification by federal formula, and the ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says Kim Jong Il in the work systematically and comprehensively dealt with the great feats performed by the President in the efforts for national reunification and indicated a correct orientation and ways to carry out the President's instructions for national reunification, adding it is an undying ideological and theoretical feat Kim Jong Il performed in the Korean nation's history of the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Korean nation is facing the historical tasks to defend and meet its common interests and develop the movement for national reunification by its concerted efforts under the uplifted banner of the June 15 joint declaration, the daily notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As indicated by the work, all the Koreans should bear deep in mind the President's instructions for national reunification and work heart and soul to successfully carry them out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should wage the struggle for national reunification according to the Juche-based line and policies set forth by the President and thus give steady continuity to the history of his leadership over the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should uphold Kim Jong Il's leadership over the struggle for national reunification single-mindedly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His leadership serves as sure guarantee for the accomplishment of the cause of national reunification. It is possible to achieve the reunification of the country despite whatever storm and stress only when the Korean people remain true to the outstanding and experienced leadership of Kim Jong Il who has successfully carried forward and implemented the idea and cause of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls on all Koreans to achieve reunification as intended by Kim Il Sung true to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

New Ice Physical Acrobatics Created
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang Circus has recently created the ice physical acrobatic suite "Young People on the Ice".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The suite consists of more than 10 items including Plastic Rotation Etude, Plastic Etude with a Ring, Stunt with Pigeons and Handstands, which show the might of the Songun Korea in a wonderful formative artistic way, and Stunt with a Whip and Rope-skipping feat based on folk amusements of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ice acrobatics showing colorful stunts and rhythmic movements to the accompaniment of beautiful music on an icy ground were put on the stage for the first time in the DPRK in July Juche 78 (1989). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The then acrobatic pieces applied in a comprehensive way the action, performance, dance and stage arts with stunt as the main. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After that ice acrobatics have developed as ice physical acrobatics in which performers' physical functions are displayed on a high stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ice physical acrobatics keep the inherent national features alive and are full of high interest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ice physical acrobatics which were performed in the form of short pieces in the past have developed into ice physical acrobatic suite which is socialist in content and national in form.

Immortal Feats Performed in Efforts to Implement President's Instruction for National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il published the famous work "Let Us Carry out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" on August 4, Juche 86 (1997). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
On this occasion, the Korean people look back with warm hearts upon the feats performed by the leader who has made imperishable patriotic true records for reunification, regarding the implementation of the instruction of President Kim Il Sung for national reunification as the supreme task. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He, in his work, formulated the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the plan of establishing the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo, which fully reflect the ideas and intention of the President for the national reunification, into the three charters for national reunification. Basing himself on this, he put forward the fundamental principles, tasks and ways to achieve the reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Over the last decade, he has upheld the banner of independence and implemented it in the reunification movement of the Korean nation in accordance with the intention of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The DPRK had to undergo the "Arduous March" and forced march caused by the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle it and natural disasters after the demise of President Kim Il Sung. In the years, he overpowered the tough policy of the anti-reunification forces with tougher one and thwarted the attempt of foreign forces to meddle in the affairs of the Korean nation and thus led the efforts to realize the dialogue, contact, cooperation and exchange between the north and the south thoroughly on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The historic Pyongyang summit in June 2000 gave a great hope and pleasure to all the fellow-countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Thanks to his energetic efforts, it resulted in making a breakthrough into the blockade between the north and the south which had been existed for 55 years and publishing the June 15 Joint Declaration, the milestone for national reunification in the 21st century, in 50-odd hours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It has become a usage that grand festivals for national reunification are held with the participation of a lot of representatives of the north, south and overseas on August 15, June 15 and other important occasions every year. And the June 15 All-Korean Committee was established as a standing and nation-wide organization for reunification movement. As a result, the efforts of the nation for reunification are being further organized and popularized. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The reality glaringly shows that the ideas and feats of the President for the national reunification are shining and the dawn for the independent reunification, the wish of the President is breaking over the 3,000-ri land of Korea under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Kim Jong Il Gives On-Site Guidance to Newly Built Hospital
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 5 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-site guidance to the newly built North Hamgyong Provincial People's Hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hospital opened some days ago is a comprehensive medical service center covering more than 50,000 square meters as it has all equipment for medical treatment and service facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il looked round the interior and exterior of the hospital for a long time to learn in detail about its internal structure and its construction. He praised the province for having built such a big hospital by its own efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There should be the best sanitary environment and convenience for the hospital as it is the most important institution related to the precious lives and health of the people but some sections do not meet these requirements, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need for the hospital to abide by the principle of isolating itself from outside and enforcing the section segregation inside it, he said that to this end, it is necessary to disallow outsiders' disorderly access to the hospital and strictly forbid people except the staff to enter the sections requiring germ-free condition including test rooms inside the hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave instructions even on settling detailed problems arising in ensuring scientific accuracy in medical treatment and creating good environment around the hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the mistake committed in the construction of the hospital was attributable to the lack of responsibility for job and serve-the-people spirit on the part of those who designed the hospital without taking the function and nature of the construction object into consideration and those who supervised it, he urged all the officials to think a lot of their work and steadily improve their technical and professional qualifications to be genuine servants for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for updating the North Hamgyong Provincial People's Hospital as intended by President Kim Il Sung so that the people in the province may fully benefit from the system of free medical care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hong Sok Hyong, chief secretary of the North Hamgyong Provincial Committee of the WPK, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee and Pak Nam Gi, department director of the WPK Central Committee.

Kim Jong Il Gives On-the-Spot Guidance to Ranam Coal Mining Machine Complex
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the Ranam Coal Mining Machine Complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He first looked round the monument to the on-the-spot guidance of President Kim Il Sung and the room devoted to its history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking back with deep emotion on the history of the development of the complex, he said it has turned into the nation's reliable large machine producer under the wise leadership of the President and his care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the production at the complex, making the rounds of the machine assembling shop and other places of the complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the successes made by the officials, workers and technicians of the complex, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they have successfully settled difficult technological problems by themselves and satisfactorily ensured the production of major custom-built equipment by strengthening creative cooperation and waging a widespread mass technical innovation movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the complex is now capable of manufacturing machine products requiring high technology by firmly consolidating the material and technological foundation of the complex, he praised the enterprising work style and fighting spirit of the officials, workers and technicians of the complex making a steady advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The heroic working class is the fighters who carry out any difficult task in good time in a do-or-die spirit with the faith that when the Party is determined to do anything, they unconditionally carry it out, he said, adding that the Korean revolution is making a steady advance along the road of big leap forward as it has such huge contingent of the working class. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks before the complex, noting that the complex has a very important duty and role to perform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hong Sok Hyong, chief secretary of the North Hamgyong Provincial Committee of the WPK, and Pak Nam Gi, department director of the WPK Central Committee.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona comandancia de Unidad No.273 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono la comandancia de la Unidad No.273 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Comandante Supremo averiguo en la sala de mando operacional como esta unidad cumple su mision y vio en la sala de leccion militar un ejercicio de mando de los oficiales del Estado Mayor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Presento las tareas para incrementar por todos los medios la combatividad de esta unidad mostrandose satisfecho de que al regularizar el entrenamiento, ella arma firmemente a todos los comandantes con los autoctonos metodos de combate para que estos adquieran la capacidad de cumplir satisfactoriamente su mision de combate bajo cualesquier circunstancias. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acto seguido, el Dirigente recorrio la casa cultural de los militares, biblioteca y otras instalaciones de cultura y educacion donde se informo de la marcha del trabajo ideo-politico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Elogio que al materializar cabalmente el metodo de trabajo politico a la manera de la guerrilla antijaponesa, la unidad forma a todos los uniformados como combatientes intransigentes y portadores de una inconmovible concepcion de la revolucion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Senalo que se registra un nuevo viraje en los rasgos ideo-politicos y el estilo de lucha de los militares del Ejercito Popular de la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar) y su poderio se ha incrementado extraordinariamente y anadio que en este mundo no hay nadie que pueda vencer a estas fuerzas armadas sin rival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Comandante Supremo se fotografio junto a los militares de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su.

Kim Jong Il recibe presente del presidente de ANL
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presente que le dirigiera el presidente de la Asamblea Nacional de la Republica Democratica Popular Lao, Thongsing Thammavong, de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El visitante lo entrego el dia 3 a Kim Yong Nam, presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea.

Kim Yong Nam se reune con delegacion de Laos
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, recibio el dia 3 en el capitalino Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae a la delegacion de la Asamblea Nacional de la Republica Democratica Popular Lao encabezada por su presidente Thongsing Thammavong, quien es miembro del Buro Politico del Comite Central del Partido Popular Revolucionario Lao, y departio con ella en un clima amistoso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion participaron el presidente del grupo de parlamentarios de amistad Corea-Laos, Kim Wan Su, y otros funcionarios asi como el encargado de negocios a.i. laosiano en Corea.
